 {"id":"bd-10h6","title":"lipgloss: Consolidate visible_width() to single canonical implementation","description":"# Task: Consolidate Three visible_width() Implementations

## Problem Statement
The crate has THREE independent implementations of ANSI-aware width calculation:

### Implementation 1: lib.rs (lines 365-417) - MOST COMPLETE
\`\`\`rust
fn visible_width(s: &str) -> usize {
    enum State { Normal, Esc, Csi, Osc }
    // Handles: Normal chars, ESC sequences, CSI sequences, OSC sequences
    // Has fast-path check for ASCII-only strings
}
\`\`\`

### Implementation 2: style.rs (lines 1965-1996) - SIMPLIFIED
\`\`\`rust
fn visible_width(s: &str) -> usize {
    enum State { Normal, Esc }
    // Only handles: Normal chars, basic ESC sequences
    // Missing: CSI parameter parsing, OSC handling
}
\`\`\`

### Implementation 3: backend.rs (lines 621-640) - MINIMAL
\`\`\`rust
fn visible_width(s: &str) -> usize {
    // Inline state tracking without enum
    // Only handles basic SGR sequences
    // No OSC handling at all
}
\`\`\`

## Risk Analysis
- **Correctness**: Different implementations may give different widths for same input
- **Maintenance**: Bug fixes must be applied to 3 places
- **Testing**: Test coverage fragmented across implementations
- **Layout**: Inconsistent widths could cause misaligned layouts

## Solution Design

### Step 1: Identify Canonical Implementation
The lib.rs version is the most complete and should be the canonical one.
It properly handles:
- Normal character width via unicode-width
- CSI sequences (SGR, cursor movement, etc.)
- OSC sequences (window title, etc.)
- Simple escape sequences (save cursor, etc.)

### Step 2: Expose as Public Function
\`\`\`rust
// In lib.rs - make public with documentation
/// Calculates the visible width of a string, excluding ANSI escape sequences.
///
/// This function correctly handles:
/// - Unicode characters with varying widths (CJK, emoji, etc.)
/// - CSI sequences (colors, cursor movement)
/// - OSC sequences (window title, hyperlinks)
/// - Simple escape sequences (save/restore cursor)
///
/// # Examples
///
/// \`\`\`rust
/// use lipgloss::visible_width;
///
/// assert_eq!(visible_width("hello"), 5);
/// assert_eq!(visible_width("\\x1b[31mred\\x1b[0m"), 3);
/// assert_eq!(visible_width("日本語"), 6);
/// \`\`\`
pub fn visible_width(s: &str) -> usize { ... }
\`\`\`

### Step 3: Replace Other Implementations
In style.rs and backend.rs, replace local implementations with calls to
the canonical version.

## Implementation Steps
1. Audit all three implementations for any unique features
2. Merge any missing features into lib.rs version
3. Add comprehensive doc comments
4. Make lib.rs visible_width() public
5. Replace style.rs and backend.rs implementations with imports
6. Add comprehensive test suite
7. Remove dead code

## Testing Strategy

### Unit Tests (Comprehensive)
\`\`\`rust
#[cfg(test)]
mod visible_width_tests {
    use super::visible_width;

    // Plain text
    #[test]
    fn plain_ascii() {
        assert_eq!(visible_width("hello"), 5);
        assert_eq!(visible_width(""), 0);
        assert_eq!(visible_width(" "), 1);
    }

    #[test]
    fn plain_unicode() {
        assert_eq!(visible_width("日本語"), 6);      // CJK
        assert_eq!(visible_width("café"), 4);       // Accented
        assert_eq!(visible_width("🎉"), 2);         // Emoji
        assert_eq!(visible_width("e\\u{0301}"), 1); // Combining mark
    }

    // SGR (Select Graphic Rendition) sequences
    #[test]
    fn sgr_colors() {
        assert_eq!(visible_width("\\x1b[31mred\\x1b[0m"), 3);
        assert_eq!(visible_width("\\x1b[1;32;44mbold green on blue\\x1b[0m"), 18);
    }

    #[test]
    fn sgr_256_color() {
        assert_eq!(visible_width("\\x1b[38;5;196mred256\\x1b[0m"), 6);
    }

    #[test]
    fn sgr_rgb_color() {
        assert_eq!(visible_width("\\x1b[38;2;255;0;0mrgb red\\x1b[0m"), 7);
    }

    // CSI (Control Sequence Introducer) sequences
    #[test]
    fn csi_cursor_movement() {
        assert_eq!(visible_width("\\x1b[10Ctext"), 4);  // Cursor forward
        assert_eq!(visible_width("\\x1b[2Jcleared"), 7);  // Clear screen
    }

    // OSC (Operating System Command) sequences
    #[test]
    fn osc_window_title() {
        assert_eq!(visible_width("\\x1b]0;My Title\\x07text"), 4);
        assert_eq!(visible_width("\\x1b]0;My Title\\x1b\\\\text"), 4);  // ST terminator
    }

    #[test]
    fn osc_hyperlink() {
        // OSC 8 hyperlinks
        assert_eq!(visible_width("\\x1b]8;;https://example.com\\x07link\\x1b]8;;\\x07"), 4);
    }

    // Edge cases
    #[test]
    fn empty_and_whitespace() {
        assert_eq!(visible_width(""), 0);
        assert_eq!(visible_width("   "), 3);
        assert_eq!(visible_width("\\t"), 1);  // Tab = 1 character
    }

    #[test]
    fn mixed_content() {
        let mixed = "\\x1b[31m日本語\\x1b[0m and text";
        assert_eq!(visible_width(mixed), 15);  // 6 (JP) + 9 ( and text)
    }

    #[test]
    fn malformed_escapes() {
        // Incomplete escape - should count visible parts
        assert_eq!(visible_width("\\x1b"), 0);
        assert_eq!(visible_width("\\x1b["), 0);
        assert_eq!(visible_width("text\\x1b"), 4);
    }

    // Performance fast path
    #[test]
    fn ascii_fast_path() {
        let ascii = "a".repeat(1000);
        assert_eq!(visible_width(&ascii), 1000);
    }
}
